Definition: quick or skillful or adept in action or thought
Example: an exceptionally adroit pianist; an adroit technician; his adroit replies to hecklers won him many followers; an adroit negotiator
Synonyms: noun, cognition, adroitness, MALADROIT, ARTFUL, quick, or, skillful, adept, in, action, thought, an, exceptionally, adroit, pianist, technician, his, replies, to, hecklers, won, him, many, followers, negotiator
Category: adj.all
